WEBVTT

00:01.750 --> 00:05.750
♪♪

00:05.750 --> 00:06.920
Hey!

00:08.040 --> 00:09.540
Great show.

00:09.540 --> 00:12.080
Dan?

00:12.080 --> 00:13.750
W-What are you
doing here?

00:13.750 --> 00:15.420
I've never seen you
perform.

00:15.420 --> 00:17.330
And you were only
212 miles away,

00:17.330 --> 00:19.960
so I thought I'd swing by.

00:19.960 --> 00:21.080
These are for you.

00:21.080 --> 00:23.380
[ Chuckles ]

00:23.380 --> 00:25.460
Why do they have nacho cheese
on them?

00:27.040 --> 00:30.120
A-A-And they
smell like beer.

00:30.120 --> 00:33.620
After I saw you
kissing the keyboard player...

00:33.620 --> 00:35.540
I threw them
in the trash.

00:35.540 --> 00:37.210
But then I fished them out
'cause, damn it,

00:37.210 --> 00:39.380
I came here
to tell you something,

00:39.380 --> 00:42.580
and maybe it's too late,
but I'm gonna tell you anyway.

00:42.580 --> 00:44.000
I'm ready.

00:46.880 --> 00:48.540
Oh.

00:48.540 --> 00:49.670
You're ready.

00:49.670 --> 00:52.040
Yeah, I thought about
what you said,

00:52.040 --> 00:54.380
and I want
a full-on relationship, too.

00:54.380 --> 00:56.120
So, what,

00:56.120 --> 00:58.330
I'm just supposed to forget
about this last year,

00:58.330 --> 00:59.960
when you've been
stringing me along,

00:59.960 --> 01:01.920
and now you're ready?

01:01.920 --> 01:04.750
So I just jump on your bike
and we ride away?

01:04.750 --> 01:08.960
Well, I'm a little saddle sore
from riding for three hours.

01:08.960 --> 01:10.750
Maybe we could hit it fresh
tomorrow?

01:12.170 --> 01:13.040
[ Sighs ]

01:13.040 --> 01:14.380
I'm sorry, Dan.

01:14.380 --> 01:16.290
Oh, come on.

01:16.290 --> 01:18.080
Come on, you gotta still feel
something for me.

01:19.540 --> 01:21.000
It's too late.

01:21.000 --> 01:22.120
I moved on.

01:25.000 --> 01:26.880
Guess you'll
want these back.

01:28.790 --> 01:30.000
No, you can keep 'em.

01:32.000 --> 01:33.460
Please don't make me.

01:35.710 --> 01:37.040
There's a Band-Aid
in here.

01:42.500 --> 01:50.880
♪♪

01:50.880 --> 01:59.250
♪♪

01:59.250 --> 02:07.710
♪♪

02:07.710 --> 02:14.250
♪♪

02:16.080 --> 02:17.920
"The Conners" is recorded

02:17.920 --> 02:20.250
in front of
a live studio audience.

02:20.250 --> 02:23.040
Okay, okay, I haven't slept
in a couple days.

02:23.040 --> 02:25.080
Uh, tell me
I'm not hallucinating.

02:25.080 --> 02:27.920
That is a man
racing a bear

02:27.920 --> 02:30.580
on an obstacle course,
right?

02:30.580 --> 02:32.380
Yeah, yeah.

02:32.380 --> 02:34.920
It's a show called
"Man vs. Bear."

02:34.920 --> 02:37.250
And they --
they do tug of war,

02:37.250 --> 02:40.880
they roll barrels up hills,
climb trees.

02:40.880 --> 02:43.670
Doesn't the bear win
most of the time?

02:43.670 --> 02:46.670
Oh, the bear wins every time.
It's a bear.

02:46.670 --> 02:48.330
I don't think
the guy's got a chance

02:48.330 --> 02:52.080
unless they introduce Sudoku
or driving a car.

02:52.080 --> 02:54.540
I think circus bears
can drive cars.

02:54.540 --> 02:55.920
You can learn anything

02:55.920 --> 02:57.540
if your food supply
depends on it.

02:57.540 --> 02:58.830
[ Laughs ]

02:58.830 --> 03:02.210
What are you guys doing?
It's 1:00 in the morning.

03:02.210 --> 03:04.120
Beverly Rose is teething,
and she won't sleep.
[ Sighs ]

03:04.120 --> 03:06.830
And you were snoring,
so I came downstairs.

03:06.830 --> 03:07.920
I don't snore.

03:07.920 --> 03:09.540
Oh.

03:09.540 --> 03:11.790
Well, then, somebody was
trimming trees in the bedroom.

03:11.790 --> 03:13.750
Let me take her
for a bit.

03:13.750 --> 03:15.040
Thanks.
Ooh.

03:15.040 --> 03:17.210
Trust me, Darlene.
You snore.

03:17.210 --> 03:18.500
When we shared a room,

03:18.500 --> 03:22.250
I used to put my old
makeup sponges in your mouth.

03:22.250 --> 03:24.500
That's okay.
I used to use your toothbrush.

03:24.500 --> 03:25.750
So?

03:25.750 --> 03:27.080
To clean the turtle bowl.

03:28.290 --> 03:30.540
[ Laughs ]

03:30.540 --> 03:31.960
Why didn't you wake me up?

03:31.960 --> 03:33.380
I tried.

03:33.380 --> 03:35.210
I nudged you. I shook you.
I pinched you.

03:35.210 --> 03:36.790
I even splashed water
on you.

03:36.790 --> 03:39.620
Oh, that explains
a very weird dream I was having.

03:39.620 --> 03:41.670
I was wrestling
with a sea otter,

03:41.670 --> 03:43.670
and then he threw his martini
in my face.

03:46.330 --> 03:48.330
"Woman vs. Otter"!

03:48.330 --> 03:50.290
That could be a show!

03:50.290 --> 03:52.120
Yes! [ Laughs ]

03:52.120 --> 03:53.670
And I know where
to get an otter.

03:53.670 --> 03:55.920
All I need is a distraction
and a big towel.

03:55.920 --> 03:57.670
[ Both laughing ]

04:02.830 --> 04:04.330
Okay.

04:04.330 --> 04:06.540
Okay, I-I-I'll put
a couple pillows under my head

04:06.540 --> 04:07.620
so I don't snore.

04:07.620 --> 04:09.000
Now come back to bed.

04:09.000 --> 04:12.000
Oh, just a few more minutes,
'cause in the last round,

04:12.000 --> 04:13.920
they each have to
give a cat a bath.

04:15.330 --> 04:17.500
This is why
we're not getting pregnant --

04:17.500 --> 04:20.040
'cause your sperm's too stupid
to find my egg.

04:22.380 --> 04:24.380
Ben!

04:24.380 --> 04:25.830
Ben, Ben!

04:25.830 --> 04:27.580
They're about to put the salmon
down in front of them

04:27.580 --> 04:29.250
for the fish-eating contest.

04:29.250 --> 04:30.790
I think the man
really has a chance here --

04:30.790 --> 04:32.170
[ Bear growls ]
Bear won.

04:32.170 --> 04:34.540
Yep.
[ Chuckles ]

04:34.540 --> 04:39.830
♪♪

04:39.830 --> 04:41.620
Last call.
Nuh-unh!

04:43.920 --> 04:47.000
It's only 2:00 in the morning.
Last call's not till 4:00.

04:47.000 --> 04:48.170
It's last call for you.

04:49.750 --> 04:53.790
Fine. I'll take three beers
and three more shots.

04:53.790 --> 04:56.580
You get one beer
and one shot.

04:56.580 --> 04:59.500
And maybe you should call your
wife so she can pick you up.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.120
I'm just staying
at the hotel next door,

05:01.120 --> 05:02.290
and my wife's dead.

05:02.290 --> 05:03.290
[ Clears throat ]

05:03.290 --> 05:04.920
You didn't kill her,
did you?

05:06.380 --> 05:07.710
No!

05:07.710 --> 05:10.710
I'm sorry. We're right off
the expressway. We gotta ask.

05:12.960 --> 05:14.380
Can I get a beer, please?

05:15.420 --> 05:17.500
Hey!

05:17.500 --> 05:19.540
You're with the band,
aren't ya?

05:19.540 --> 05:20.710
Yeah.

05:20.710 --> 05:22.170
What'd you think
of the show?

05:22.170 --> 05:23.920
I love Louise.

05:24.960 --> 05:26.620
She is the lead singer.

05:26.620 --> 05:29.380
Nobody ever loves
the keyboard player.

05:29.380 --> 05:32.460
Seems like somebody's
loving the keyboard player.

05:32.460 --> 05:34.290
I saw Louise kissing you.

05:34.290 --> 05:36.620
And I gotta be honest
with you --

05:36.620 --> 05:38.420
it really bothered me.

05:38.420 --> 05:40.670
Oh,
you're one of those guys.

05:40.670 --> 05:41.960
I know.

05:41.960 --> 05:44.290
It looks like
she's singing directly to you,

05:44.290 --> 05:46.170
but she's just trying
to remember the words.

05:48.710 --> 05:50.710
It's not
what you're thinking.

05:50.710 --> 05:52.540
This is us.

05:52.540 --> 05:55.710
We dated a little
back in Lanford.

05:55.710 --> 05:59.000
Yeah, I didn't have the guts
to commit.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.670
And then I gave her
cheese flowers

06:01.670 --> 06:04.540
and really
messed things up.

06:04.540 --> 06:06.620
Cheese flowers?

06:06.620 --> 06:09.460
Is that something, like,
that another guy could catch?

06:10.710 --> 06:11.960
No, nothing like that.

06:11.960 --> 06:13.920
Look...

06:13.920 --> 06:15.920
I just want her back.

06:17.880 --> 06:18.960
Do you love her?

06:20.290 --> 06:22.080
I don't know...

06:22.080 --> 06:24.330
drunk guy.

06:24.330 --> 06:26.080
We've been friends
for a long time,

06:26.080 --> 06:28.330
and this just happened,
and, uh...

06:28.330 --> 06:29.580
it's got
nothing to do with you.

06:29.580 --> 06:32.040
Okay! Okay!

06:32.040 --> 06:34.580
I get it.
Backing off.

06:34.580 --> 06:36.500
Beep, beep, beep.

06:37.960 --> 06:40.040
Oh, do me a favor,
will ya?

06:40.040 --> 06:41.880
The next time you see her,

06:41.880 --> 06:45.580
tell her that
Dan's not afraid to say it.

06:45.580 --> 06:47.000
"I love you."

06:47.000 --> 06:50.080
But her, not you.

06:50.080 --> 06:51.920
I-I love her, not you.

06:53.040 --> 06:54.710
[ Grumbles ]

06:54.710 --> 06:58.500
It's you talking,
but it's me saying it.

06:58.500 --> 07:00.040
You'll do that for me,
right?

07:00.040 --> 07:01.290
No.

07:02.500 --> 07:04.380
Aw, come on!

07:04.380 --> 07:05.500
What's your name?

07:05.500 --> 07:06.250
Zach.

07:06.250 --> 07:09.620
Zach,
I'd do it for you.

07:09.620 --> 07:10.920
Watch.

07:10.920 --> 07:12.540
Marla.

07:12.540 --> 07:14.540
Zach loves you.

07:14.540 --> 07:19.000
Yeah, after midnight,
everybody loves me.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.080
Good luck to you,
buddy.

07:21.080 --> 07:22.460
Oh, thanks!

07:22.460 --> 07:24.250
Oh! Oh!

07:24.250 --> 07:26.460
Oh, I feel like you and I

07:26.460 --> 07:29.330
have made
a little connection here.

07:29.330 --> 07:32.420
It may be the beer talking,
but I think I love you, too.

07:32.420 --> 07:34.080
[ Chuckles ]

07:37.420 --> 07:38.960
♪♪

07:38.960 --> 07:40.500
What are
all the pills for?

07:40.500 --> 07:43.920
They're vitamins to increase
my odds of getting pregnant.

07:43.920 --> 07:46.040
So, you're actually
trying now?

07:46.040 --> 07:48.420
You know,
the world has enough kids.

07:48.420 --> 07:50.210
The Earth can barely sustain
what we've got.

07:50.210 --> 07:52.330
What the hell, woman?

07:52.330 --> 07:55.380
Ben and I want to have
a baby together,

07:55.380 --> 07:57.000
and it's gonna be
a really small one,

07:57.000 --> 08:00.830
so it's not gonna use up
a lot of resources.

08:00.830 --> 08:03.080
And we'll recycle it
when we're done.

08:04.210 --> 08:05.750
You're being
really selfish.

08:05.750 --> 08:08.040
Lay off, Harris!

08:08.040 --> 08:10.670
I'm just saying.
Adopt one, don't drop one.

08:12.710 --> 08:14.250
Look, I'm 43.

08:14.250 --> 08:16.000
I don't even know
if I can have a baby, okay?

08:16.000 --> 08:17.210
Get off my back.

08:19.080 --> 08:21.420
Your old people sex
is destroying the Earth!

08:23.620 --> 08:26.330
We're not gonna be here
that long, so we don't care!

08:28.330 --> 08:30.120
Hey, you gotta get dressed
for the meeting.

08:30.120 --> 08:32.250
We're gonna be late.
We gotta leave like right now.

08:32.250 --> 08:34.500
I am sorry.
I went to bed way too late.

08:34.500 --> 08:36.420
Beverly Rose fell asleep
in my arms.

08:36.420 --> 08:38.170
I didn't want to move
and wake her up.

08:38.170 --> 08:40.080
Well, you could have
given her to Becky.

08:40.080 --> 08:42.210
Oh, I didn't mind.
Becky needed a break.

08:42.210 --> 08:43.830
You go on ahead.
I'll meet you there.

08:43.830 --> 08:45.420
But, hey, don't forget
I am coming with you

08:45.420 --> 08:47.170
to your doctor's appointment
afterwards.

08:47.170 --> 08:49.380
You don't need to go to that.
I'll fill you in later.

08:49.380 --> 08:51.250
Just don't be late
for the meeting.

08:51.250 --> 08:53.040
We need this guy's
advertising dollars.

08:53.040 --> 08:54.750
Well, hey, it --
it is an adult bookstore,

08:54.750 --> 08:56.670
so if you get there before I do,
just talk about

08:56.670 --> 08:58.290
what a shame it is
people don't read anymore.

09:00.120 --> 09:02.670
There's something wrong with
the hot water in the house,

09:02.670 --> 09:04.000
and I need a shower real bad

09:04.000 --> 09:05.920
because Beverly Rose
threw up in my hair,

09:05.920 --> 09:07.620
and I tried running it
and running it,

09:07.620 --> 09:09.040
and no hot water
came out.

09:09.040 --> 09:10.920
And if I don't get a shower
and some sleep,

09:10.920 --> 09:12.000
I'm gonna eat the baby.

09:13.540 --> 09:15.920
Nobody is eating
any babies.

09:15.920 --> 09:17.500
It is probably just
the pilot light.

09:17.500 --> 09:19.120
I'll check it.

09:19.120 --> 09:20.920
[ Sighs ]

09:22.500 --> 09:24.000
[ Grunts ]

09:24.000 --> 09:25.620
Yeah.
It's the pilot light.

09:25.620 --> 09:27.250
This'll just
take a second.

09:27.250 --> 09:30.710
Now, we just turn this,
hold the button down,

09:30.710 --> 09:32.170
and...it's out.

09:32.170 --> 09:33.290
[ Sighs ]
Alright.

09:33.290 --> 09:35.670
So, uh...

09:35.670 --> 09:37.620
it's a little more complicated
than I thought.

09:37.620 --> 09:39.380
Uh, but as soon as I get back
from the meeting with Darlene,

09:39.380 --> 09:40.380
I'll fix it.

09:40.380 --> 09:42.790
You said
you could fix this!

09:42.790 --> 09:44.540
Were you just talking
out of your ass,

09:44.540 --> 09:47.000
like all men do?!

09:47.000 --> 09:48.670
[ Crying ]
I just want a shower!

09:48.670 --> 09:52.750
I just want my hair to smell
like pretty apples again!

09:52.750 --> 09:54.250
Okay, okay!

09:54.250 --> 09:57.210
Maybe I can try and fix it
right now, okay?

09:57.210 --> 09:59.420
Could just be
a clogged burner.

09:59.420 --> 10:02.500
So, I'm just gonna
reach in there...

10:02.500 --> 10:04.170
[ Grunts ]

10:04.170 --> 10:05.830
Wow.

10:05.830 --> 10:07.290
Well, that came out
way too easy.

10:07.290 --> 10:09.540
[ Crying loudly ]

10:14.830 --> 10:17.460
Hey, rom-com!

10:17.460 --> 10:19.580
I heard you rode
all the way to Springfield

10:19.580 --> 10:21.830
to tell Louise
you couldn't live without her.

10:21.830 --> 10:23.460
Did you catch her
at the airport

10:23.460 --> 10:26.460
before she flew to Paris
to marry the wrong guy?

10:26.460 --> 10:28.880
Why are you screaming?

10:28.880 --> 10:30.830
Oh, a little hung over

10:30.830 --> 10:32.540
from all the celebrating,
are we?

10:32.540 --> 10:34.620
Well, I guess some people
can't hold a case of beer

10:34.620 --> 10:36.080
like they used to.

10:36.080 --> 10:39.460
Actually, I got drunk
with Louise's new boyfriend.

10:39.460 --> 10:41.250
Oh!

10:41.250 --> 10:43.750
Dan, let me tell you something
from personal experience --

10:43.750 --> 10:45.830
thrupples don't work.

10:45.830 --> 10:47.500
No thrupples.

10:47.500 --> 10:49.040
No couples.

10:49.040 --> 10:50.540
No nothing.

10:50.540 --> 10:51.790
She moved on.

10:51.790 --> 10:53.620
Oh, man!

10:53.620 --> 10:55.500
I'm sorry. Dan!

10:55.500 --> 10:57.380
I told her
I was ready to commit.

10:57.380 --> 10:59.960
She was tired of waiting.

10:59.960 --> 11:02.380
I'm never gonna meet
anyone like her again.

11:02.380 --> 11:04.880
Okay, look, you got
your heart broken.

11:04.880 --> 11:06.250
That sucks.

11:06.250 --> 11:08.500
But if nothing else,

11:08.500 --> 11:11.420
you learned that you're ready to
let somebody in your life now.

11:11.420 --> 11:12.880
Maybe it won't be somebody
like her.

11:12.880 --> 11:14.210
Maybe it'll be somebody

11:14.210 --> 11:16.540
a little more, you know,
your speed.

11:16.540 --> 11:19.540
Like a lady ranch hand

11:19.540 --> 11:21.120
or...

11:21.120 --> 11:22.960
baggage handler.

11:22.960 --> 11:25.920
I'm not looking for somebody
to help me move a couch.

11:25.920 --> 11:27.380
Okay, I'm just saying

11:27.380 --> 11:29.460
now that you're open
to all the possibilities,

11:29.460 --> 11:30.830
you're gonna
find somebody.

11:30.830 --> 11:32.250
[ Sighs ]

11:32.250 --> 11:33.960
Jackie, you've been open
to all the possibilities

11:33.960 --> 11:35.210
for 40 years.

11:35.210 --> 11:36.170
How's that working out
for you?

11:36.170 --> 11:38.170
We're not talking
about me!

11:38.170 --> 11:40.000
I'm out of
my freakin' mind!

11:40.000 --> 11:43.670
I wouldn't know the first thing
about meeting someone.

11:43.670 --> 11:45.420
Hmm. Interesting.

11:45.420 --> 11:48.790
As Lanford's former
leading life coach,

11:48.790 --> 11:51.460
I'd say the fact that
you're grabbing a beer...
[ Bottle cap pops ]

11:51.460 --> 11:53.000
...when we're talking
about relationships

11:53.000 --> 11:55.120
is very significant.

11:55.120 --> 11:56.540
Oh, please!

11:56.540 --> 11:59.120
It's hops and barley.
They're grains.

11:59.120 --> 12:00.750
You put them in a bowl,
you're a health nut.

12:00.750 --> 12:02.000
You put them in a bottle,

12:02.000 --> 12:04.580
you're running away
from your feelings.

12:04.580 --> 12:08.000
Look, I know that
it can be intimidating,

12:08.000 --> 12:10.250
but there's a lot
of women waiting to
meet somebody like you,

12:10.250 --> 12:11.830
and we're all looking
for the same thing --

12:11.830 --> 12:13.580
somebody
who doesn't play games,

12:13.580 --> 12:16.170
somebody who's
emotionally available,

12:16.170 --> 12:19.000
and most especially,

12:19.000 --> 12:22.170
somebody who doesn't wear
a wedding ring.

12:23.920 --> 12:25.120
I don't know
if I can do that.

12:25.120 --> 12:26.540
[ Sighs ]

12:26.540 --> 12:28.540
Dan,
taking off the ring --

12:28.540 --> 12:32.620
it's not gonna erase
all the wonderful memories

12:32.620 --> 12:34.710
that you had
with Roseanne.

12:36.500 --> 12:41.500
Your age and drinking history's
gonna do that.

12:41.500 --> 12:42.670
[ Laughing ]

12:45.250 --> 12:48.710
♪♪

12:51.500 --> 12:53.790
Where's Ben?
I don't know.
I'm watching Mark.

12:53.790 --> 12:54.790
Well, where's Mark?

12:54.790 --> 12:56.290
I have no idea.

12:58.000 --> 13:00.080
Could be with Ben.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.920
Can you believe
that Ben missed a meeting

13:02.920 --> 13:04.420
that he knew was important

13:04.420 --> 13:06.620
because he had to fix
the water heater?

13:06.620 --> 13:08.710
I'm so fed up with him.

13:08.710 --> 13:11.040
He spends more time
with Becky and her damn baby

13:11.040 --> 13:13.290
than he does getting
our stupid magazine set up.

13:13.290 --> 13:15.040
I know
we've gone over this,

13:15.040 --> 13:17.040
and I think this is
one of those times

13:17.040 --> 13:18.670
where I'm just
supposed to listen.

13:20.500 --> 13:21.750
Do you know where Ben is?

13:21.750 --> 13:22.580
In the basement.

13:22.580 --> 13:24.210
With Becky?

13:24.210 --> 13:26.380
Yeah. She blew up her life,
so that's where she lives now.

13:32.880 --> 13:34.290
Hey, you're home.

13:34.290 --> 13:35.710
You got my texts, right?

13:35.710 --> 13:37.540
Yeah, I got 'em.

13:37.540 --> 13:39.670
Well, I was waiting for you
to text me back.

13:39.670 --> 13:42.210
Well, I was a little busy
trying to woo a porn merchant.

13:42.210 --> 13:44.250
Can I talk to you for a sec?
In private?

13:44.250 --> 13:45.670
