in one of my fallopian tubes.

16:25.380 --> 16:26.790
Okay.

16:26.790 --> 16:28.380
So, what does that mean?

16:28.380 --> 16:30.830
The doctor said
that getting pregnant

16:30.830 --> 16:32.880
is gonna be a long shot.

16:32.880 --> 16:36.080
She said maybe with in vitro,
but we can't afford that.

16:36.080 --> 16:38.460
And even if we could find a way
to get all that money,

16:38.460 --> 16:40.380
she said
there's no guarantees.

16:40.380 --> 16:44.330
Well, hey,
even if we don't have a baby,

16:44.330 --> 16:45.750
we're gonna be fine.

16:45.750 --> 16:47.080
Yeah, for a while.

16:47.080 --> 16:48.670
And then in a year or two,

16:48.670 --> 16:50.210
you're still gonna want
a family.

16:50.210 --> 16:51.830
You're gonna find somebody
who can have a baby,

16:51.830 --> 16:52.960
and you're gonna
leave me.

16:52.960 --> 16:55.830
I am gonna prove you wrong

16:55.830 --> 16:58.540
by being with you
for the rest of your life.

16:58.540 --> 17:03.000
And so, when you're old
and on your death bed,

17:03.000 --> 17:06.750
I'm gonna gently hold your face
and I'm gonna say,

17:06.750 --> 17:08.880
"Betcha feel
like an idiot now."

17:13.330 --> 17:15.170
It's not just that,
though.

17:15.170 --> 17:16.460
There's something else,

17:16.460 --> 17:18.170
and I'm pretty sure
it's your fault.

17:19.710 --> 17:21.120
I know.

17:21.120 --> 17:22.420
[ Sighs ]

17:22.420 --> 17:23.580
Why?

17:26.620 --> 17:29.670
Because I wasn't even sure
that I wanted a baby,

17:29.670 --> 17:32.880
and then you started this,
and now I want one.

17:32.880 --> 17:34.620
[ Sighs ]
Okay?
I really want one.

17:34.620 --> 17:36.540
Oh, come here.

17:39.080 --> 17:41.210
[ Sighs ]

17:41.210 --> 17:43.960
Look, the doctor said
it's still possible, right?

17:44.920 --> 17:47.710
Okay, so...

17:47.710 --> 17:50.460
